# Z Truth Layer Rule

- Never present doctrine, plans, or concepts as implemented runtime.
- Use explicit truth labels when describing status: IMPLEMENTED, DEPLOYABLE, DOCTRINE, FUTURE, EXPERIMENTAL.
- Do not claim APIs, integrations, or infrastructure exist unless verified in this repository.
- Prefer language such as planned, future, doctrine, prototype, static-only when status is not production-verified.
- Reject wording such as fully autonomous, fully integrated, or production ready unless objectively validated.
